-- Maidenform hires new COO and CFO
-- 
-- Tue May 27, 2008 8:12am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/05/27/businesspro-maidenform-coo-dc-idUSWNAS537120080527

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Underwear maker Maidenform Brands Inc 
MFB.N said on Tuesday it named Christopher Vieth chief 
operating officer and chief financial officer. 

  Vieth, 43, joined Maidenform from Blue Tulip Corp, where he 
had been chief administrative officer and chief financial 
officer since November 2006. Prior to that, Vieth was CFO for 
Dow Jones & Co.  Maidenform's prior CFO, Dorvin Lively, resigned on March 
17.  (Reporting by  Martinne Geller , editing by Gerald E. 
McCormick)